[{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis-Neural-Signal-Analysis","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#API-Reference","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","text":"Modules = [NeuroAnalysis]","category":"page"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.ColorMaps","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.ColorMaps","text":"Predefined ColorMaps\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.CondDCh","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.CondDCh","text":"Default digital input channels\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.SecondPerUnit","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.SecondPerUnit","text":"Time Unit set to millisecond by default.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"},{"location":"#Base.range-Union{Tuple{Vararg{T, N} where N}, Tuple{T}} where T<:ColorTypes.Colorant","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"Base.range","text":"Generates linearly interpolated colors between key colors inclusively.\n\nreturn an Array of colors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.alphablend-Tuple{ColorTypes.Colorant, ColorTypes.Colorant}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.alphablend","text":"alpha weighted average of foreground and background colors\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.alphamask-Tuple{Matrix{var\"#s32\"} where var\"#s32\"<:ColorTypes.Colorant}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.alphamask","text":"Masking alpha channel of an image, match the implementation in Experica shaders.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.assignlayer-Tuple{Any, Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.assignlayer","text":"Try to locate cell layer.\n\ny coordinate of cell postion\nlayer definition\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.cas-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.cas","text":"2D cas function defined as cas(x+y) = cos(x+y) + sin(x+y)\n\nkx: Frequency in cycle/unit_x\nky: Frequency in cycle/unit_y\nphase: Phase of a cycle in [0, 1] scale\nisnorm: scale cas in [-√2, √2] to [-1, 1]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.cas-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.cas","text":"cas function defined as cas(x) = cos(x) + sin(x)\n\nf: Frequency in cycle/unit_x\nphase: Phase of a cycle in [0, 1] scale\nisnorm: scale cas in [-√2, √2] to [-1, 1]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.cas2sin-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.cas2sin","text":"2D cas to 2D sin gratingf\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.cas2sin-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.cas2sin","text":"cas phase to sin phase, phase is in [0, 1] scale\n\nnote: Note\ncas(x) = 2 sin(x + π4)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.checkcircuit-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.checkcircuit","text":"Check circuit consistency and remove duplicates\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.checklayer!-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.checklayer!","text":"Check Layer Boundaries\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.chmasknp-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.chmasknp","text":"Logical mask for Neuropixels channels in probe shape\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.circaxial","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.circaxial","text":"Transforms p-axial data to a common scale   α: sample of angles in radians   p: number of modes\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.circaxialmean","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.circaxialmean","text":"Mean direction for circular data with axial\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.circmean","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.circmean","text":"Mean for circular data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.circr","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.circr","text":"Mean Resultant Vector Length for circular data     α: sample of angles in radians     w: number of incidences in case of binned angle data     d: spacing of bin centers for binned data, if supplied        correction factor is used to correct for bias\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.circtuningfeature-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.circtuningfeature","text":"Properties of Circular Tuning\n\n- Prefered Direction/Orientation\n- Selectivity Index\n    - version 1: (ResponsePrefered - ResponseOpposing)/ResponsePrefered\n    - version 2: (ResponsePrefered - ResponseOpposing)/(ResponsePrefered + ResponseOpposing)\n- Half Width at Half Peak-to-Trough\n\nx: angles in radius\ny: responses\n\nod: opposing angle distance, π for DSI, 0.5π for OSI\nfn: factor name\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.circvar","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.circvar","text":"Circular Variance\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.clamproi-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.clamproi","text":"Confine ROI radius so that ROI is within the image\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.clampscale-Tuple{Any, Real, Real}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.clampscale","text":"clamp value to min and max, and linearly map range [min, max] to [0, 1]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.complexmap-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.complexmap","text":"Complex sum of angles and corresponding image responses\n\nimage responses [height, width, n]\nangles in radius [n]\n\ncenterfun: function to get center for sdfactor (median)\npresdfactor: center +- sdfactor * sd, for clamping before filtering\nfilter: filter kernel\nsufsdfactor: center +- sdfactor * sd, for clamping after filtering\nresponsesign: increasing/decreasing(+/-) response\n\nreturn complex map, angle map, and magnitude map\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condfactor-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condfactor","text":"Get factors of conditions\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condimageresponse-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condimageresponse","text":"Mean image responses of each conditions\n\nrs: responses of each epoch [height, width, nepoch]\nci: epoch indices of repeats for each condition\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condin-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condin","text":"In Condition Tests, find each unique condition, number of repeats and its indices\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condresponse-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condresponse","text":"Group repeats of Conditions, get Mean and SEM of responses\n\nrs: responses of each trial\nci: trial indices of repeats for each condition\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condstring-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrameRow}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condstring","text":"Print Condition in String\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condtest-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condtest","text":"Get CondTest DataFrame\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.condtestcond-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.condtestcond","text":"Get CondTestCond DataFrame\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.correlogram-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.correlogram","text":"Shift(shuffle) corrected, normalized(coincidence/spike), condition/trial-averaged Cross-Correlogram of binary spike trains. (Bair, W., Zohary, E., and Newsome, W.T. (2001). Correlated Firing in Macaque Visual Area MT: Time Scales and Relationship to Behavior. J. Neurosci. 21, 1676–1697.)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.csd-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.csd","text":"1D Current Source Density for a set of voltage traces from a linear array of electrodes.\n\ndata: ch x sample or ch x sample x epoch(volts)\n\nmethod:\n\nCSD: finite difference method of second spatial derivatives of potentials, I = - ∇σ⋅∇ϕ,       σ is conductivities, ϕ is potentials, on the continuous assumption when spacing is around 20-100 um.      (Nicholson & Freeman, 1975, J Neurophysiol, 38(2): 356-68)\n\niCSD: solve I -> ϕ forward problem, then get the inverse transformation matrix.       (Petterson et al., 2006, J Neurosci Methods, 154(1-2):116-33)\n\n  iCSDdelta: δ method where infinitely thin current source discs of radius r.\n  iCSDspline: cubic spline method where current source between electrode be modeled by smooth spline\n\nkCSD: kernal CSD       ()\n\nh: channel spacing(micrometers)\nc: conductivity of the extracellular medium in siemans/meter\nr: radius(micrometers) of the model current source/sink in reverse method\nreturn: CSD(amps/meters^3)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.csd_cubicspline","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.csd_cubicspline","text":"cubic spline inverse CSD\n\ncontact_positions: contact positions data: measured potentials Fcs: cubic spline transformation matrix corresponding to the given contact positions E0,E1,E2,E3: matrixes containing the \"recursive rules\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.ctctc-Tuple{Dict, Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.ctctc","text":"Get CondTest and CondTestCond DataFrame\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.dft-Tuple{Any, Any, Vararg{Any, N} where N}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.dft","text":"Discrete Fourier Transform at frequencies\n\nDFTk = sum_n=0^N-1 xn e^frac-2Pi inkN k = 0N-1 N = length(x) fₛ sampling x fₖ = fₛN sampling DTFT\n\nsignal\nsimpling frequency of signal\nat which frequencies DFT are directly evaluated\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.digitalbit-Tuple{Any, Any, Vararg{Any, N} where N}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.digitalbit","text":"Parse bit event time and value.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.digitaldata-Tuple{Dict, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.digitaldata","text":"Get digital channel time and value.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.dirsigtest-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.dirsigtest","text":"Direction tuning significance using dot product with empirical orientation preference This function calculates the probability that the \"true\" direction tuning vector of a neuron has non-zero length. It performs this by empirically determing the unit orientation vector, and then computing the dot product of the direction vector for each trial onto the overall orientation vector, and then looking to see if the average is non-zero.\n\nInputs:  ANGLES is a vector of direction angles at which the response has        been measured.        RATES is the response of the neuron in to each angle; each row        should contain responses from a different trial. Output:  P the probability that the \"true\" direction tuning vector is        non-zero.\n\nSee: Mazurek, Kagan, Van Hooser 2014;  Frontiers in Neural Circuits\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.dogf-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.dogf","text":"Difference of Gaussians function\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.dropmatdim!-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.dropmatdim!","text":"Drop array dims according to MATLAB convention.\n\nscalar: scalar instead of 1x1 array\nrvector: vector instead of 1xN array\ncvector: vector instead of Nx1 array\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.e_matrixes-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.e_matrixes","text":"Computes the E0, E1, E2 and E3 matrixes used in the cubic spline iCSD method. These matrixes contains the recursive formulas for finding the F matrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epoch2sampleindex-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epoch2sampleindex","text":"Convert epochs in time to sample index\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochsample-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochsample","text":"Epochs of Channel Sample.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochsamplenp-NTuple{4, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochsamplenp","text":"Epochs of Neuropixels Channel Sample x, optionally gain corrected(voltage), line noise(60,120,180Hz) removed and bandpass filtered\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrain-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrain","text":"Epochs of a Spike Train in between binedges\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrain-Tuple{Any, Real, Real}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrain","text":"Epoch of a Spike Train x, where min <= x[i] < max.\n\nkwargs isminzero, ismaxzero and shift set epoch zero value to min+shift or max+shift.\n\nreturn:\n\ny: epoch of the Spike Train\nn: number of elements in the epoch, or divided by duration(max-min) of the epoch, based on kwargs israte\nw: epoch window(min,max)\ni: indices of epoch elements in the original Spike Train, such that y = x[i]\n\nSee also: epochspiketrains, epochspiketrainresponse\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrainresponse-Tuple{Any, AbstractMatrix{T} where T}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrainresponse","text":"Response of each epoch of a Spike Train, could be mean firing rate or number of spikes based on kwarg israte.\n\nSee also: epochspiketrainresponse_ono\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrainresponse_ono-Tuple{Any, AbstractMatrix{T} where T}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrainresponse_ono","text":"Response of each epoch of a Spike Train, could be mean firing rate or number of spikes based on kwarg israte.\n\nnote: Note\nThis is a faster(~500x) version compared to epochspiketrainresponse, but only works when x, mins and maxs are ascendingly ordered, and each maxs-mins range are none-overlapping.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrains-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.epochspiketrains","text":"Epochs for each Spike Trains\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.exchmasknp-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.exchmasknp","text":"Logical mask for Neuropixels excluded channels in probe shape\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.exd-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.exd","text":"extrema value of max amplitude and it's delay index\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.expericafileregex-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.expericafileregex","text":"Regular Expression to match Experica data file name\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.f1orisf-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.f1orisf","text":"Estimate the F1 Ori and SpatialFreq of an image from its 2D powerspectrum.\n\nx: 2D powerspectrum\nfreqd1: frequencies of dim 1\nfreqd2: frequencies of dim 2\n\nreturn:\n\nori: Orientation in radius, 0 is -, increase counter-clock wise\nsf: SpatialFreq along the line perpendicular to ori\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.f_cubicspline","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.f_cubicspline","text":"F and E matrix of the cubic spline inverse CSD\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.factorresponse-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.factorresponse","text":"Condition Response in Factor Space\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.factorresponsefeature-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.factorresponsefeature","text":"Tuning properties of factor response\n\nfl: factor levels\nfr: factor responses\nHueAngle, Orientation and Direction follow the same convention such that 0 is -/→, then increase counter-clock wise.\nFor cases where Orientation and Direction are interlocked(drifting grating):      - when Orientation is -(0), then Direction is ↑(90)      - when Direction is →(0), then Orientation is |(-90)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.finalfactor-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.finalfactor","text":"Get Final factors of conditions\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.findclosestangle-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.findclosestangle","text":"find the index i in thetas that thetas[i] is closest to a, all in radius\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.findcond-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.findcond","text":"Find Condition with Factor=level\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.fitmodel-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.fitmodel","text":"Fit 1D model to data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.fitmodel2-Tuple{Any, Matrix{T} where T, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.fitmodel2","text":"Fit 2D model to image\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.flatspiketrains","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.flatspiketrains","text":"Flat Spike Trains to SpikeTimes and Trials, optionally sort trial based on sv\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.flin-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.flin","text":"Find levels for each factor and indices, repetition for each level\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.frameresponse-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.frameresponse","text":"Frame Response, (R - R₀) / R₀\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.gaborf-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.gaborf","text":"Gabor function\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.gaincorrectnp-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.gaincorrectnp","text":"Convert raw Neuropixels data to gain-corrected voltages. The saved-channel id subset in data will be used to get corresponding gain.\n\nThe full conversion with gain is:\n\ndataVolts = dataInt * fi2v  gain\n\nNote that each channel may have its own gain.\n\ny: the saved data stream, excluding the last Sync channel.\nmeta: corresponding meta for y\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.gaussianf-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.gaussianf","text":"Gaussian function\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.getdatafile-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.getdatafile","text":"Get matched file names in path\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.getexpericafile-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.getexpericafile","text":"Get matched Experica files in directory\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.getoifile-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.getoifile","text":"Get Optical Imaging VDAQ matched files in directory\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.goodnessoffit-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.goodnessoffit","text":"Goodness of Fit Metrics:\n\nr: Pearson Correlation Coefficient\nmae: Mean Absolute Error\nrmse: Root Mean Squared Error\nrae: Relative Absolute Error\nrse: Relative Squared Error\nr2: R Squared\nadjr2: Adjusted-R²\ns: Residual Standard Error\naic: Akaike Information Criterion\nbic: Bayesian Information Criterion\n\ny: responses\nŷ: model predictions\n\nn: sample size\ne: errors(y - ŷ)\nk: number of predictors\ndf: degree of freedom(n - k - 1)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.grating-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.grating","text":"Generate Grating Image, match the implementation in Experica grating shader.\n\nθ: Orientation (radius), 0 is -, increase counter-clock wise\nsf: SpatialFreq (cycle/deg)\ntf: TemporalFreq (cycle/sec)\nt: Time (second)\nphase: Phase of a cycle in [0, 1] scale\nsize: Tuple of image size in degree\nppd: pixel per degree\nisnorm: return image in [0, 1] or [-1, 1]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.gratingf-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.gratingf","text":"2D sin grating function\n\nθ: Orientation in radius, 0 is -, increase counter-clock wise\nf: Frequency in cycle/unit_x/y\nphase: Phase of a cycle in [0, 1] scale\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.gratingf-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.gratingf","text":"sin grating function\n\nf: Frequency in cycle/unit_x\nphase: Phase of a cycle in [0, 1] scale\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.gvmf-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.gvmf","text":"Generalized von Mises function [1]\n\nf(α) =  βe^κ₁(cos(α - μ₁) - 1) + κ₂(cos2(α - μ₂) - 1)\n\n[1]\n\nGatto, R., and Jammalamadaka, S.R. (2007). The generalized von Mises distribution. Statistical Methodology 4, 341–353.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.halfwidth-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.halfwidth","text":"left and right half width of v relative to y[start], -Inf/Inf when no v is found.\n\nstart: index of y which is the center of the width\nv: value on which width is cutoff\ncirc: whether y is defined on circular domain and width can wrap around\nx: domain of y, return width when x provided, otherwise return cutoff indices\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.hartley-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.hartley","text":"Generate gratings in Hartley space (PL)\n\nkx, ky: wavenumber along x, y axis\nbw: black and white (phase) flip\nstisize: stimulus size in visual angle (degree); note that sz[1]=sz[2]\n\nif norm=true,Return image in [0,1], otherwise return image in [-1,1]\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.hartleysubspace-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.hartleysubspace","text":"Generate Hartley Subspace, where k is frequency in cycle/unit_x/y. [1]\n\nkbegin: k >= kbegin\nkend: k <= kend\ndk: Δk, step on k axis\nphase: phase in [0, 1] scale, default 0.\nshape: :square or :circle shape subspace\naddhalfcycle: add half cycle shifted hartleys\nblank: the element of hartley as blank, default uniform gray.\nnblank: number of blanks to add\n\n[1]\n\nRingach, D.L., Sapiro, G., and Shapley, R. (1997). A subspace reverse-correlation technique for the study of visual neurons. Vision Research 37, 2455–2464.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.hlpass-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.hlpass","text":"High pass and low pass filtering\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.hotellingt2test","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.hotellingt2test","text":"Hotelling's T-Squared test for one multivariate sample.\n\nPerforms Hotelling's T^2 test on multivariate samples X to determine if the data have mean MU.  X should be a NxP matrix with N observations of P-dimensional data, and the mean MU to be tested should be 1xP. the significance level α is 0.05 by default.\n\nH is 1 if the null hypothesis (that the mean of X is equal to MU) can be rejected at significance level α.  P is the actual P value.\n\nThe code is based on HotellingT2.m by A. Trujillo-Ortiz and R. Hernandez-Walls.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.ismodulative-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.ismodulative","text":"Check if any factors and their interactions significently modulate response using ANOVA\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.isresponsive-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.isresponsive","text":"Check if any sub group of response is significently different from baseline by Wilcoxon Signed Rank Test\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.isresponsive-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.isresponsive","text":"Check if response is significently different from baseline by Wilcoxon Signed Rank Test\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.isresponsive-Tuple{Matrix{T} where T, Vector{T} where T}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.isresponsive","text":"Check if std of a spatial-temporal kernal within response time window significently different from that of the baseline time window\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.loadimageset-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.loadimageset","text":"Load images in directory\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.localcontrast-Tuple{Any, Integer}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.localcontrast","text":"local RMS contrast of each image, highlighting local structure regions\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.maptodatatime-Tuple{Any, Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.maptodatatime","text":"Map time to data timeline, optionally add latency.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.matchfile-Tuple{Regex}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.matchfile","text":"Get matched file names in directory, optionally join directory to get file path\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.matdictarray2df-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.matdictarray2df","text":"convert Matlab struct of array to DataFrame\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.mergeroi-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.mergeroi","text":"Get the minimum ROI region encompass all rois\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.normalized-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.normalized","text":"Normalize values of an array to be between -1 and 1\n\noriginal sign of the array values is maintained.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.oifileregex-Tuple{}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.oifileregex","text":"Regular Expression to match Optical Imaging VDAQ block file name\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.parsedigitalinanalog","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.parsedigitalinanalog","text":"Get digital rising and falling edges in a analog stream return di: edges index        dv: edges active/inactive state\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.peakroi-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.peakroi","text":"peak ROI region and its delay index\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.plotanalog-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.plotanalog","text":"Plot Analog Signals\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.plotcondresponse-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.plotcondresponse","text":"Plot Mean and SEM of responses for each condition\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.plothartleysubspace-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.plothartleysubspace","text":"plot hartley subspace\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.plotspiketrain-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.plotspiketrain","text":"scatter plot of spike trains\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.poissonspiketrain-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.poissonspiketrain","text":"Generate a Poisson Spike Train\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.powerspectrum-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.powerspectrum","text":"Multi-Taper power spectrum estimation\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.powerspectrum2-Tuple{Matrix{T} where T, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.powerspectrum2","text":"2D powerspectrum of an image.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.powerspectrums2-Tuple{Vector{T} where T, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.powerspectrums2","text":"2D powerspectrums of images in same size.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.prepare-Tuple{AbstractString, Vararg{Any, N} where N}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.prepare","text":"Read and Prepare Dataset in MATLAB MAT File\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.prepare_experica!-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.prepare_experica!","text":"Prepare Experica Experiment Data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.prepare_oi!-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.prepare_oi!","text":"Prepare Optical Imaging Block Data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.prepare_ripple!-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.prepare_ripple!","text":"Prepare Ripple Data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.psthspiketrains-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.psthspiketrains","text":"PSTH of Spike Trains\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.readmat-Tuple{AbstractString, Vararg{Any, N} where N}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.readmat","text":"Read variables of a MATLAB MAT file into a Dictionary\n\nf: MAT file path\nvars: variable names in the varset to read\n\nvarset: variable names to select in vars\nscalar: scalar instead of 1x1 matrix\nrvector: vector instead of 1xN matrix\ncvector: vector instead of Nx1 matrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.readmeta-Tuple{AbstractString}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.readmeta","text":"Read DataExport Metadata MAT File\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.ref2sync","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.ref2sync","text":"Map time between ref and target, according to the timing diff between target and ref of the same sync signal\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.refchmasknp-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.refchmasknp","text":"Logical mask for Neuropixels reference channels in probe shape\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.reshape2mask-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.reshape2mask","text":"reshape data stream in the same shape of chmask, where masked channels are replaced with local average\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.rmline!-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.rmline!","text":"Remove line noise and its harmonics by notch filter\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.roccurve-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.roccurve","text":"This function calculates the ROC curve, which represents the 1-specificity and sensitivity of two classes of data, (i.e., class1 and class2).\n\nThe function also returns all the needed quantitative parameters: threshold position, distance to the optimum point, sensitivity, \tspecificity, accuracy, area under curve (AROC), positive and negative predicted values (PPV, NPV), false negative and \tpositive rates (FNR, FPR), false discovery rate (FDR), false omission rate (FOR), F1 score, Matthews correlation coefficient \t(MCC), Informedness (BM) and Markedness; as well as the number of true positives (TP), true negatives (TN), false positives (FP), \tand false negatives (FN).\n\nRewrite from Víctor Martínez-Cagigal (2020). ROC Curve, MATLAB Central File Exchange. Retrieved February 11, 2020.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.roiwindow-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.roiwindow","text":"Get ROI from indices\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sampleindex2time-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sampleindex2time","text":"sample index to time\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sbxexd-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sbxexd","text":"Find the extreme value\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sbxjoinhartleyFourier-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sbxjoinhartleyFourier","text":"Peichao:\n\nJoin the results from differernt Hartleys after hartleyFourier analysis\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sbxpeakroi-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sbxpeakroi","text":"peak ROI region and its delay\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sftuningfeature-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sftuningfeature","text":"Properties of Spatial Frequency Tuning\n\n- Prefered Spatial Frequency\n- Half Width at Half Peak-to-Trough\n- Freq Passing Type {A:All Pass, H:High Pass, L:Low Pass, B:Band Pass}\n- Bandwidth ``log2(H_cut/L_cut)``\n- Passwidth at Half Peak-to-Trough constrained by low freq lim and high freq lim\n\nx: sf in cycle/degree\ny: responses\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sin2cas-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sin2cas","text":"2D sin gratingf to 2D cas\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sin2cas-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sin2cas","text":"sin phase to cas phase, phase is in [0, 1] scale\n\nnote: Note\ncas(x) = 2 sin(x + π4)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.sta-Tuple{AbstractMatrix{T} where T, AbstractVector{T} where T}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.sta","text":"Spike Triggered Average of Images\n\nx: Matrix where each row is one image\ny: Vector of image response\n\nnorm: normalization factor, default no normalization.       it could be sum(y) if y is number of spike or spike rate, then STA would be spiking probability.\nwhiten: whiten factor, default no whiten.       it could be (xᵀx)¹ or inverse of covariance matrix, that decorrelate STA.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.statetime-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.statetime","text":"Extract state time of condtest\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.stfilter-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.stfilter","text":"Spatial and Temporal filter of data stream\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.time2sampleindex-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.time2sampleindex","text":"time to sample index\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.unitspike_kilosort-Tuple{Dict}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.unitspike_kilosort","text":"Organize each spiking unit from Kilosort result.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.vlabregex-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.vlabregex","text":"Regular expression to match VLab data file names\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.vmeanse-Tuple{AbstractMatrix{T} where T}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.vmeanse","text":"Vertical Mean and SEM of a matrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.vmf-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.vmf","text":"von Mises function [1]\n\nf(α) =  βe^κ(cos(n(α - μ)) - 1)\n\n[1]\n\nSwindale, N.V. (1998). Orientation tuning curves: empirical description and estimation of parameters. Biol Cybern 78, 45–56.\n\nβ: amplitude at μ\nμ: angle of peak\nκ: width parameter\nn: frequency parameter\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#NeuroAnalysis.vstack-Tuple{Any}","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis.vstack","text":"Vertical stack same length vectors to matrix\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PlotUtils.cgrad-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{T, T}} where T<:ColorTypes.Colorant","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"PlotUtils.cgrad","text":"Generates linearly interpolated ColorGradient\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#PlotUtils.cgrad-Union{Tuple{Vararg{T, N} where N}, Tuple{T}} where T<:ColorTypes.Colorant","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"PlotUtils.cgrad","text":"Generates linearly interpolated ColorGradient between key colors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Index","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","title":"NeuroAnalysis - Neural Signal Analysis","text":"Modules = [NeuroAnalysis]","category":"page"}]
